In their archives, they referred to the 1966 Supreme Court decision on Dr. Sheppard's verdict, because of the breadth of the process, and wanted to clarify the requirement that new media require new rules.
"This case," they wrote, "represents the case of Sheppard versus Maxwell of the 21st century."
