The partyism and direction is greater today than it was in the mid-1990s, and it turns out that a greater ideological divide has been created between Obama and the parliamentary Republicans than it was in the case of the Republicans and Bill Clinton.
At the same time, activists on both sides see 2010 as a prelude to more important elections in 2012.
Based on this reality, the courtesy that emerged this week would welcome many Americans.
But it will cost a lot of effort on both sides to find common ground in the issues that still divide them.
