Early next year, the court will begin investigating Nuon Che, Khieu Samphan, Ieng Sary and his wife, Ieng Thirith, another former Khmer Rouge minister.
The court is mandated to prosecute the head of the representative and the people responsible for the crimes, but it has not been said whether it will continue in the four cases.
It was not enough to calm the fears in Anlong Venge.
