"There is peace and stability in Cambodia," she said.
"If there are further prosecutions, there will be war."
Prime Minister Hun Sen, who defected from the Khmer Rouge in 1978, also repeatedly warned that there would be instability if the court looked for other suspects, although experts and historians disagree.
