The WikiLeaks case has two meanings.
On the one hand, there is an obvious scandal, a scandal that seems to be a scandal only in the face of the hypocrisy that governs relations between states, citizens and the press.
On the other hand, it speaks of profound changes at the international level, and predicts a future controlled by regression.
