The rule that secret documents should consist only of reports already known is fundamental in the dynamics of the secret services, and not only in this century.
When you go to a bookstore dedicated to esoteric literature, you will see that each work repeats (about the Grail, the riddle of Rennes-le-Ch<0xC3><0xA2>teau, the Templars or the Masons) exactly what was already written in previous works.
